narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned how to better communicate, write, and understand the Yoruba Language, as well as learning more about Yoruba grammar, culture, and syntax.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Oluseye was a delight to learn from and I enjoyed every second I spent in his classroom. Oladoyin Abiona also helped to make this class incredible, helping students when they were in need and trying to give everyone a chance at succeeding. Weaknesses: The course can be sparatic with work distributions, having little work one week and a lot another.
strengths: you learn the language weaknesses: n/a

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I loved this class and I recommend it to anyone looking to take a foreign language. As foreign languages go there is probably more tedious work than other classes. But it is not overall stressful and it is a relaxing environment. The teacher helps you succeed and keeps class so fun. I actually enjoyed going to class everyday because it was so funny.
I would. It is an interesting course with an incredible professor. If one is looking for an interesting new language to learn, this would be the choice for you.
